 and climate change (1997) Geophys Res Lett, 24, pp. 3057-3060; Trenberth, K.E., Caron, J.M., Stapaniak, D.P., Worley, S., Evolution of El Niño-Southern Oscillation and global atmospheric surface temperatures (2002) J Geophys Res, 107, pp. D8. , 10.1029/2000JD000298; Tsonis, A.A., Dynamical systems as models for physical processes (1996) Complexity, 1, pp. 23-33; Tsonis, A.A., Fractality in nature (1998) Science, 279, pp. 1614-1615; Tsonis, A.A., Elsner, J.B., Chaos, strange attractors, and weather (1989) Bull Amer Meteor Soc, 70, pp. 16-23; Tsonis, A.A., Elsner, J.B., Global temperature as a regulator of climate predictability (1997) Physica D, 108, pp. 191-196; Tsonis, A.A., Elsner, J.B., Comments on ""the southern oscillation as an example of a simple ordered subsystem of a complex chaotic system"" (1998) J Climate, 11, pp. 2453-2454; Tsonis, A.A., Roebber, P.J., Elsner, J.B., A characteristic time scale in the global temperature record (1998) Geophys Res Lett, 25, pp. 2821-2823; Tziperman, E., Stone, L., Cane, M.A., Jarosh, H., El Nino chaos: Overlapping of resonances between the seasonal cycle and the Pacific ocean-atmosphere oscillator (1994) Science, 264, pp. 72-74; Tziperman, E., Scher, H., Zebiak, S.E., Cane, M.A., Controlling spatio-temporal chaos in a realistic El Niño prediction model (1997) Phys Rev Lett, 79 (6), pp. 1034-1037; Tziperman, E., Cane, M.A., Zebiak, S.E., Xue, Y., Blumenthal, B., Locking of El Niño's peak time to the end of the calendar year in the delayed oscillator picture of ENSO (1998) J Climate, 11, pp. 2191-2199; (1997) UCAR Quarterly El Niño and Global Warming: What's the Connection, 24. , UCAR office of programs, winter; Viswanathan, G.M., Afanasyev, V., Buldyrev, S.V., Murphy, E.V., Prince, P.A., Stanley, H.E., Levy flight search patterns of wandering albatrosses (1996) Nature, 381, pp. 413-415; Walker, G.T., Correlation in seasonal variations of weather III: A preliminary study of worldwide weather (1923) Mem Indian Meteorol Dep, 